\series bold
Baby-MAKRO
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Help from Martin Kirk Bonde and Peter Stephensen from the DREAM group have
 been invaluable for writing this note.
 Anders Buch JÃ¼rs has provided excellent research assistance.
 Comments from students working with the model has also improved it considerably
 (Andreas Marius Laursen, Hans Christian Jul Lehmann, Mathias Held Berg,
 Nicholas Stampe Meier, Olivier Ding, Ufuk Yasin).
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series default
\size normal
\emph on

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

DISCLAIMER: WORK-IN-PROGRESS 
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

 BEWARE OF ERRORS!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Jeppe Druedahl
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
This note outlines a simplified 
\begin_inset Quotes ald
\end_inset

baby
\begin_inset Quotes ard
\end_inset

 version of the MAKRO model used by the Danish Ministry of Finance.
 The model is for a small open economy with a fixed exchange and overlapping
 generations.
 The model have perfect foresight, but is full of imperfections due to e.g.
 frictions in the labor market and adjustment costs.
 The model is written and solved in terms of a series of ordered blocks.
 This clarifies the model dynamics and make it easier to solve for fluctuations
 around the steady state using a numerical equation system solver.
 Online code is provided for solving the model in Python.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The model is designed so undergraduate students can work with it, and analyze
 potential extensions in their thesis work.
 The model structure is similar to state-of-the-art heterogeneous agent
 models (see this 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "course"
target "https://sites.google.com/view/numeconcph-advmacrohet/"
literal "false"

\end_inset

) and the model is thus relevant for further academic studies.
 The similarity to the grown-up MAKRO model make it relevant for potential
 future job tasks and the public debate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The note concludes with a status report on the continuing development of
 the model.
\end_layout

